load ../pattern-body-surface.maude

--- COVERAGE 1: a body of only allow-listed constructs is accepted.
search [1] in PATTERN-BODY-SURFACE :
  admit(ruleC effectC recordC schemaC)
  =>*
  accepted .

--- COVERAGE 2: a workflow terminal in the body is rejected.
search [1] in PATTERN-BODY-SURFACE :
  admit(terminalC)
  =>*
  rejected .

--- COVERAGE 3: a forbidden construct dominates an otherwise-allowed body.
search [1] in PATTERN-BODY-SURFACE :
  admit(ruleC terminalC recordC)
  =>*
  rejected .

--- COVERAGE 4: a workflow contract in the body is rejected.
search [1] in PATTERN-BODY-SURFACE :
  admit(contractC)
  =>*
  rejected .

--- COVERAGE 5: a nested pattern declaration is rejected.
search [1] in PATTERN-BODY-SURFACE :
  admit(nestedPatternC)
  =>*
  rejected .

--- COVERAGE 6: a nested pattern application is rejected.
search [1] in PATTERN-BODY-SURFACE :
  admit(nestedApplyC)
  =>*
  rejected .

--- BITE 1: an allow-listed-only body is NEVER rejected.
--- `rejected` is a reachable verdict elsewhere (coverage 2-6), so this search
--- genuinely explores the reachable set and finds no match.
search [1] in PATTERN-BODY-SURFACE :
  admit(ruleC effectC recordC schemaC)
  =>*
  rejected .

--- BITE 2: a body containing a forbidden construct is NEVER accepted.
search [1] in PATTERN-BODY-SURFACE :
  admit(ruleC terminalC)
  =>*
  accepted .
